The paper deals with neural network optimization and pruning, which are core topics in machine learning and deep learning. Specifically, the paper proposes a novel method for network pruning at initialization, which is relevant to the subfield of neural architecture search and design. The experiments are conducted on image classification datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves some aspects of natural language processing, as it mentions the use of the CIFAR-10 and CIFAR-100 datasets, which are commonly used in NLP research. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also possible sub-categories, although less likely than the first three.
